                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13216862" author="jdonofrio" created="Sun, 26 Feb 2012 21:40:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes I agree we should change all test assert failures to throw AssertionError instead of mixing IOException and assert failures as RuntimeExceptions&lt;br/&gt;
We just have to change throw new RuntimeException(buffer.toString()); to fail(buffer.toString()); in TestDriver and update the test to catch AssertionError&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13217076" author="jarcec" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2012 06:55:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 (I also agree that it would make more sense to use AssertionError rather than IOException or RuntimeException)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13220657" author="jdonofrio" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 04:06:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can we change this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13222951" author="jdonofrio" created="Tue, 6 Mar 2012 02:56:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am going to make this change, 3 of us are in agreement and no users have responded on mrunit-user since you sent the email 2 week ago on Feb 27&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13223014" author="brocknoland" created="Tue, 6 Mar 2012 05:59:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13225851" author="jdonofrio" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2012 05:17:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed validate to use JUnit fail method instead of throws RuntimeException&lt;br/&gt;
Removed throws RuntimeException on runTests methods&lt;br/&gt;
added ExpectedSuppliedException class to better test exceptions&lt;br/&gt;
fixed test methods to use ExpectedSuppliedException to test for AssertionError along with correct message in the exception&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13225852" author="jdonofrio" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2012 05:18:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed in 1298706&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
